snippet.textDisplay:
I once got robbed of almost everything we had while in Athens Greece!


legit no joke, all our passports were gone, almost all of our money, my moms purse (with her iPad, phone and my phone in it), and a whole backpack full of random stuff we had were all stolen and we had to stay there for another 2 weeks to get our new passports and go home. it was even worse then what I described because I can't remember shit, but yeah, that was a bad day XD





another bad TIME was when our 2002 7.3L ford f350 long bed got stolen after us having it for 8 long beautiful years. I remembered having long road trips listening to the beautiful sound of that big diesel engine while cruising at 80mph in the middle of some desert in the long roads in the Indian reservations of Arizona at midnight. then waking up, still driving and seeing the beautiful sunrise stopped at a gas station (also in the middle of nowhere) with hundreds of bugs stuck on the front of the trucks big chrome grill eating some of those Buggles or whatever they are called. I would remember just the sound of that thing in the mountains downshifting and hearing the massive stock turbo as the air is released in a satisfying lite sound of air quickly blowing and releasing the pressure from inside the turbo. most of you probably don't have a clue what I'm talking about, but I think everyone can tell I loved that thing very much, and I can confidently say that when we did get the truck back... and I saw it full of wires and removed interior panels and a destroyed ignition (not to mention how the poor thing drove, it wouldn't get out of 4wd low, which if you don't know, if very bad to be driving on the road... symptoms may include tires slipping while going around a corner, high revs for no reason, and generally scariness when driving on any mountain road to do with those 2 things). needless to say, after all, that I have been through with that truck and with all the trips we have gone on with it... and seeing what the people who stole it did to it... I wanted to find them and beat them over the head with the bad battery that they also swapped out while taking the good one we had (it takes 2 big batteries) aaannnddd I wouldn't regret it 1 bit




yeah s those are 2 things that have happened off the top of my head that was really bad. the second one probably wouldn't be such a big deal if I weren't very into cars, and didn't get attached to things like that. but I tried explaining it in the most accurate way possible to show how sad it would have been for me when I found out it was stolen. honestly, I was kinda more sad about the truck being stolen then us being robbed because although we got about $21,000 for that truck through insurance, there arent any other trucks just like it around I could find. it has a banks tune with gages, it was black, it was a long bed, it had the 7.3l Powerstroke v8 (the best diesel v8 ever made imo), it was a lariat with leather seats (cloth seats from that era were disgusting), and had still had the sweet smell of high quality leather, like in an old Mercedes-Benz. it also had all the memories we had with it over the past 8 years attatched, even ones from WAYYY back (we once had a 5th wheeler, and we have had that truck for an additional 5 year since that was gone, with the years we had with the trailer).


ok, this is going too long so ima end it here, everyone who has made it this far, thanks for reading what I had to say or for just pressing the "read more" and coming straight down here XD. either way, I hope you have a good rest of your day and peace out ✌
